As ſure as can be you will bring ſomething


                  from amongst the Records of the Obſolete Gothick Feudal-Laws,
Reaſons why the Rector of P. took the Oath of Allegiance. and would infer that it muſt needs ſignifie at this day ſome Active, Warlike Endeavours in behalf of the Soveraign; becauſe the tenure of thoſe times was upon Condition that the Tenant ſhould attend his Lord to the Wars, and the Security they gave to perform this, was ſwearing to bear faith and true Allegiance to them.

By the Divine Law; and that contrary to the Law of England;
                  P. 26. for the Hiſtorian ſhews, that both the Siſters were declared illegitimate, and that by Act of Parliament; and were they not ſo, yet being

but of the Half-blood to the King, by the Law they could not ſucceed.
